Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.16,0:00:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,SPECTRA. Raw I/Q in, threat picture out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.17,0:00:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Marine FOB Spectrum Awareness — what is in my bubble, is any of it not\Nours?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.17,0:00:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Six synthetic 1-second I/Q captures. NIST SigMF schema.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.30,0:00:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,STFT renders the spectrogram. SigMF header on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Multimodal model ingests the spectrogram plus the SigMF header.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.34,0:00:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Strict JSON: modulation, protocol, anomaly flag, confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.34,0:00:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hero model drafts a SIPR-format Spectrum Awareness Brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.34,0:00:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,BLUF, header, top emitters, anomalies, recommended actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.35,0:00:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Three clicks: pick a capture, classify, draft the brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.40,0:00:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Unauthorized-band emitter. Cached brief loads instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.40,0:00:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL — same code, now on the Inference Mesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.40,0:01:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,IL5 / IL6 ready. ReBAC. Air-gapped. Zero data movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.40,0:01:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,SPECTRA. Built on the Kamiwaza Stack. Powered by Kamiwaza.
